column5: I saw that the weather was cool and rainy, but ususlly plenty of fish are still caught on opening weekend. Any good reports out there from LOTW or Lac Seul ? I'm going up in a week and need some hype to give me some sleepless nights ! Thanks

My boat counted 682 walleyes caught in Lac Seul. Biggest 27.75 inch, a lot of slot fish. 80% were 12-16 inch range, I guess they have to eat too!. We fished Sawmill and the mouth of the river. Good luck Spuds

We were northwest of Lac Suel...Shabumeni Lake...read this post to get a little juiced up...I know the feeling...I just sent one of my best friends off to go up to Fawcett Lake for the next week...http://www.inshore-fishing.com/forum...924b66cf416750 Rob
Great report and pictures. Now I can't wait for my trip to get here. Mike
Yeah, gets me going too. That one quote asks what kind of bait to catch the mooose on. I know!! "Mooskie" baits of course.
Looks great. next month for us. cant wait.
